  "aboutParagraphs": [
    "I'm Robert, a second-year Economics and Psychology student at Claremont McKenna College and a Robert Day and Henry R. Kravis Scholar. I grew up in Pomona as a first-generation American, and that shapes how I think about opportunity and what business can do for people.",
    "In 2021, my sister and I started Cariño Botánica, a zero-waste refill store serving the Inland Empire. Running it has been one of the best teachers I've had. I've learned more about operations, systems, and what actually works than I could in any classroom. I also work with Claremont Sustainability Consulting and stay involved with Scholars of Finance and CMC's Breakfast Club.",
    "I'm interested in consulting because I like figuring out how things work, solving problems that matter, and working with people who care about what they do. Outside of school and business, I perform with Mariachi Serrano, paint and make pottery when I have time, garden, and stay active through rock climbing, running, and yoga.",
	"This site collects some of the work and projects I've done. Thanks for being here!"
  ],
