        "I co-founded Cariño Botánica in 2021 with my sister to bring zero-waste, accessible essentials to the Inland Empire. We started at a small booth in Downtown Pomona and grew into a refillery serving communities that often lack sustainable options. I've handled everything from vendor sourcing and product research to operations, finances, web design, events, and customer service.",
        "My work taught me how to build systems from the ground up, balance mission with margins, and design for real accessibility. It's been one of the most challenging and formative experiences in understanding what it takes to run a business rooted in community and purpose."
